cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY 

The paper discusses a new approach to supervising neural networks in computer vision tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The approach involves specifying constraints derived from prior domain knowledge, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The tasks involve detecting and tracking objects, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the challenges of encoding prior knowledge into appropriate loss functions, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
